      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The big tech companies strongly counter that their success is due to superior innovation and consumer preference, not anti-competitive tactics. They argue that robust competition still exists from smaller players and that their services benefit consumers through lower prices and better features. Furthermore, they contend that government intervention risks slowing down the very innovation that drives the modern economy. In short, they frame these investigations as an overreach that misunderstands how modern digital markets function.",
      "source": "target",
